        CURRENT_TAXONOMY_TEACHES_US_THAT_AT_PRESENTARU_THE                    = 12102,  -- Current taxonomy teaches us that at presentaru, the monoceros family contains few known specimens. Those that are classified exhibit great horn spire-wires jutting from their majestic heads, and are either born of light, or of darkness.
