        THROUGH_THIS_PASSAGE_YOU_LL_FIND_THE_MERCENARY                        = 12801,  -- Through this passage you'll find the mercenary barracks. Next to Heavens Tower, this place exhibits the best defenses in all Windurst. All can rest in peace, knowing that a single beastman will never make it inside!
        SALUTATIONS_I_AM_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_ALFRED_HOW              = 12802,  -- Salutations, I am Campaign Evaluation Official Alfred. How might I be of assistance?
        GREETINGS_I_AM_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_ANNABELLE_HOW             = 12803,  -- Greetings, I am Campaign Evaluation Official Annabelle. How can I help you today?
        HELLO_I_M_CAMPAIGN_EVALUATION_OFFICIAL_LLEWELLYN_HOW                  = 12804,  -- Hello, I'm Campaign Evaluation Official Llewellyn. How can I help you today?
        WHAT_DO_YOU_REQUIRE_NOTHING_AN_EVALUATION_INFO                        = 12805,  -- What do you require? Nothing. An evaluation. Info on the duration of my medal. An overview of evaluations. Info on medals. Info on the benefits of medals. Info on evaluation process.
        EVALUATIONS_ARE_CONDUCTED_ON_ALL_PARTICIPANTS_OF_THE                  = 12806,  -- Evaluations are conducted on all participants of the Allied Campaign. Individual data is collected by the Allied War Council from various sources, such as Campaign Arbiters and the leaders of the armies in which the soldiers serve. This data is then used to determine whether or not a decoration is to be conferred.
        SOME_OF_THE_AREAS_THAT_ARE_CONSIDERED_IN                              = 12807,  -- Some of the areas that are considered in this evaluation are performance in campaign operations, as well as valor shown during campaign battles.
        THE_MORE_AN_INDIVIDUAL_IS_DECORATED_THE_MORE                          = 12808,  -- The more an individual is decorated, the more responsibility he or she will be given within the Allied Forces. And with more responsibility comes the promise of larger compensation in exchange for services.
        HOWEVER_THE_PRESTIGE_THAT_ACCOMPANIES_THE_MEDALS_ALSO                 = 12809,  -- However, the prestige that accompanies the medals also carries with it a great weight. To maintain one's status, he or she must continue to exceed previous expectations. If a soldier fails to fulfill the duties that are required of all those who possess a certain medal, then the Allied War Council will be forced to confiscate that decoration.
        TO_PUT_IT_SIMPLY_ONLY_THOSE_WHO_FIGHT                                 = 12810,  -- To put it simply, only those who fight with fervor and precision...only those who put the glory of the Allied Campaign above all else...will be allowed to reap the benefits that come with victory.
        IF_YOU_WISH_TO_LEARN_MORE_OF_THE                                      = 12811,  -- If you wish to learn more of the Allied Campaign, please speak with [/Lady Fiaudie/Centurion Aurelius/Kolin-Olin].
        THERE_ARE_TWO_MORE_THINGS_OF_NOTE                                     = 12812,  -- There are two more things of note.
        ONCE_AN_EVALUATION_HAS_BEEN_REQUESTED_THE_ALLIED                      = 12813,  -- Once an evaluation has been requested, the Allied War Council will require [five days/one hour] (Earth time) to come to a conclusion.
        DURING_THAT_TIME_INDIVIDUALS_MAY_JOIN_AS_MANY                         = 12814,  -- During that time, individuals may join as many operations or battles as they wish, but will only be considered for a single medal.
        HOWEVER_THE_SAME_RULES_APPLY_FOR_AN_INADEQUATE                        = 12815,  -- However, the same rules apply for an inadequate performance. No matter how low one scores, the maximum number of decorations that can be confiscated is one.
        ALSO_INDIVIDUALS_MUST_NOT_FORGET_THAT_ALL_MEDALS                      = 12816,  -- Also, individuals must not forget that all medals come with expiration dates. While an extremely unorthodox practice, this measure was deemed necessary to prevent the forgery of allied decorations by those persons with dubious intentions.
        UPON_CONFERRAL_ALL_MEDALS_ARE_MARKED_WITH_A                           = 12817,  -- Upon conferral, all medals are marked with a magical seal that dissipates after a period of thirty days (Earth time). Once the seal has vanished, the medal will become void and its owner will no longer be able to participate in campaign operations or battles, among other things.
        IT_IS_HIGHLY_RECOMMENDED_THAT_YOU_KEEP_TRACK                          = 12818,  -- It is highly recommended that you keep track of the time remaining on your medal and apply for evaluations regularly.
        IS_THERE_ANYTHING_ELSE_YOU_WISH_TO_ASK                                = 12819,  -- Is there anything else you wish to ask?
        CAMPAIGN_MEDALS_ARE_OFFICIAL_REWARDS_GIVEN_TO_THOSE                   = 12820,  -- Campaign medals are official rewards given to those individuals who perform exemplary deeds for the Allied Forces.
        THESE_DECORATIONS_ARE_INTERNATIONALLY_RECOGNIZED_AS_SYMBOLS_OF        = 12821,  -- These decorations are internationally recognized as symbols of strength, loyalty, and honor. They not only garner respect, but provide their bearers with privileges not offered civilians.
        THOSE_WHO_HAVE_BEEN_DECORATED_WITH_THE_MORE                           = 12822,  -- Those who have been decorated with the more prestigious medals will also be highly regarded among their army's ranks, and thus entrusted with increasingly difficult and important missions.
        ON_THE_OTHER_HAND_DISLOYALTY_TO_ONE_S                                 = 12823,  -- On the other hand, disloyalty to one's nation is highly frowned upon. If, for any reason, an individual wishes to leave their current army of employment and pledge allegiance to another, they will be required to return their two most distinguished medals.
        TO_THE_POINT_ARE_WE_VERY_WELL_I                                       = 12824,  -- To the point, are we? Very well, I shall list the merits those in the possession of medals may receive.
        FIRSTLY_THE_MORE_PRESTIGIOUS_AN_INDIVIDUAL_S_MEDAL                    = 12825,  -- Firstly, the more prestigious an individual's medal, the more weight his/her] army's [/curate/supply commander/Morale Manager] will grant his/her] opinion.
        SECONDLY_THE_TYPES_OF_CAMPAIGN_OPS_AVAILABLE_TO                       = 12826,  -- Secondly, the types of Campaign Ops available to an individual will increase based on the medals that he/she] has in his/her] possession. More advanced operations will earn participants increased amounts of EXP and Allied Notes, as well as have a heavier influence on performance evaluations.
        THIRDLY_BENEFITS_RECEIVED_DURING_CAMPAIGN_BATTLES_WILL_VARY           = 12827,  -- Thirdly, benefits received during campaign battles will vary depending on the variety of medals an individual carries. The better the medals, the larger the opportunity to earn EXP, Allied Notes, and reputation. The selection of temporary items available for purchase will also improve.
        HOWEVER_THE_MORE_PRESTIGIOUS_THE_MEDAL_THE_MORE                       = 12828,  -- However, the more prestigious the medal, the more that will be expected of its bearer. The Campaign Arbiters will not go easy on those who have already proven themselves.
