        ID_13193                                                              = 13193,  -- ...
        FROM_TODAY_THE_FEDERATION_FORCES_WILL_DIVIDE_INTO                     = 13194,  -- From today, the Federation forces will divide into two hosts.
        THE_WAR_WARLOCKS_UNDER_MY_COMMAND_WILL_MARCH                          = 13195,  -- The War Warlocks, under my command, will march on the enemy, while the Mithran Mercenaries remain behind to defend the homeland...
        WITH_ONE_EXCEPTION_ROMAA_AND_THE_COBRAS_I                             = 13196,  -- ...With one exception. Romaa and the Cobras, I have chosen you to accompany me north.
        UNDERSTOOD_4                                                          = 13197,  -- Understood.
        LOOKS_LIKE_WE_VE_BEEN_TAPPED_FOR_HOUSESITTING                         = 13198,  -- Looks like we've been tapped for housesitting duty again. Borrrrrring!
        AWWW_AND_HERE_I_THOUGHT_I_D_BE                                        = 13199,  -- Awww... And here I thought I'd be able to snag the heads of another beastman general or two for my collection!
        ARE_YOU_TRULY_SO_NAIVE                                                = 13200,  -- Are you truly so naive?
        WITH_OUR_ARMY_DIVIDED_THE_CITY_DEFENSES_WILL                          = 13201,  -- With our army divided, the city defenses will be stretched thinner still. The Yagudo are not likely to overlook this...
        EXACTLY_YOU_MUST_STAY_VIGILANT_AND_BE_PREPARED                        = 13202,  -- Exactly. You must stay vigilant, and be prepared to defend the Federation at the first sign of enemy movement.
        OF_COURSE_WARLOCK_WARLORD_YOU_CAN_RRRELY_ON                           = 13203,  -- Of course, Warlock Warlord. You can rrrely on us.
        THE_REST_OF_YOU_WE_WILL_RENDEZVOUS_WITH                               = 13204,  -- The rest of you. We will rendezvous with our allies at San d'Oria for a briefing before we embark on the march northward. Ready your belongings and prepare to depart at once.
        REPORTARUS_FROM_SAN_D_ORIA_MAKE_NO_MENTION                            = 13205,  -- Reportarus from San d'Oria make no mention of any enemy movement in the north. Is this information to be trusted? Or shall we dispatch-watch our own scouts?
        THERE_IS_NO_NEED_IF_THERE_IS_ACTION                                   = 13206,  -- There is no need. If there is action, we can surely count on...her...to let us know.
        I_SEE_SO_THATARU_WAS_YOUR_PLAN_IN                                     = 13207,  -- I see...so thataru was your plan in ordering the Leonian War Warlocks to stay posty-wosted up north.
        THE_NEXT_MOVE_BELONGS_TO_THE_CONFEDERATE_BUT                          = 13208,  -- The next move belongs to the Confederate...but how will they play?
        CAN_WE_TRULY_SUCCEED_WITHOUT_CALLING_UPON_HIM                         = 13209,  -- Can we truly succeed without calling upon...him?
        ID_13210                                                              = 13210,  -- ...
        TIHL_MIHL_YOU_PAID_A_RRRECENT_VISIT_TO                                = 13211,  -- Tihl, Mihl. You paid a rrrecent visit to San d'Oria, did you not? I'll be counting on you two to lead the way.
        YESSIR_BOSS_SIR_WE_VE_GOT_IT_COVERED                                  = 13212,  -- Yessir, boss sir! We've got it covered, rrright, Mihl?
        LEAVE_IT_TO_ME_I_KNOW_THOSE_STRRREETS                                 = 13213,  -- Leave it to me! I know those strrreets like the back of my paw!
        WELL_LOOKS_LIKE_WE_RE_MAKING_THE_TRRRIP                               = 13214,  -- Well, looks like we're making the trrrip to San d'Oria together again, eh %?
        IT_ALMOST_SEEMS_LIKE_FATE_Y_KNOW_LIKE                                 = 13215,  -- It almost seems like fate, y'know? Like we were destined to become trrraveling companions...
        THERE_YOU_GO_AGAIN_WITH_THE_SAPPY_SENTIMENTALITY                      = 13216,  -- There you go again with the sappy sentimentality, Tihl. You should hear her around the camp, %. Always bragging about how you're her best frrriend.
        OH_YEAH_AND_WHAT_S_WRONG_WITH_THAT                                    = 13217,  -- Oh yeah? And what's wrong with that, huh!?
        TEEHEEHEE                                                             = 13218,  -- Teeheehee!
        LOOKS_LIKE_WE_RRRE_OFF_TO_SAN_D                                       = 13219,  -- Looks like we'rrre off to San d'Oria together again, eh, %? Who'd'a thunk it? Teeheehee!
        I_MEAN_IT_S_NOT_EVERY_DAY_THAT                                        = 13220,  -- I mean, it's not every day that a Mithra like me gets to bond with someone from your part of the world, rrright?
        TRAVELING_TO_FAR_OFF_LANDS_GOOD_FRIENDS_AT                            = 13221,  -- Traveling to far-off lands, good friends at your side... I shouldn't say it, but at times like this I almost feel like this war isn't all bad, y'know?
        ARE_YOU_MERCENARIES_OR_LITTLE_KITTENS_ON_A                            = 13222,  -- Are you mercenaries or little kittens on a picnic? Enough with the vapid prrrattle!
        YOU_HEARD_THE_WARLOCK_WARLORD_WE_LL_BE                                = 13223,  -- %, you heard the Warlock Warlord. We'll be waiting for you in San d'Oria!
        WHY_ARE_YOU_STILL_PUTTERRRING_ABOUT_HERE_DIDN                         = 13224,  -- %? Why are you still putterrring about here? Didn't you hear the Warlock Warlord's orders? All Cobras are to make for San d'Oria at once!
        FORT_KARUGO_NARUGO_IS_ON_HIGH_ALERT_AND                               = 13225,  -- %! Fort Karugo-Narugo is on high alert, and you're still rrrunning around here with your tail between your legs!? All Cobras are to move out at once! That's an order!
        AH_JUST_THE_PERSON_I_WAS_HOPING_TO                                    = 13226,  -- Ah, %. Just the person I was hoping to see!
        I_WAS_JUST_ON_MY_WAY_TO_RRRUN                                         = 13227,  -- I was just on my way to rrrun a very important errand. Why don't you come with me?
        IN_FACT_I_INSIST                                                      = 13228,  -- In fact, I insist.
        WHERE_TO_YOU_ASK_WHY_TO_PAY_OUR                                       = 13229,  -- Where to, you ask? Why, to pay our rrrespects to none other than the Star Sibyl.
        DO_I_MAKE_MYSELF_CLEAR_INSIDE_THE_STAR                                = 13230,  -- ...Do I make myself clear? Inside the Star Sibyl's chamber, you are to be on your absolute besty-west behavior!
        WELCOME_MY_CHILDREN                                                   = 13231,  -- Welcome, my children.
        YOU_ARE_THE_WARLOCK_WARLORD_S_ADVISOR_LEHKO                           = 13232,  -- You are the Warlock Warlord's advisor. Lehko Habhoka, was it not? Your loyal service to Windurst has not gone unnoticed in these chambers.
        I_AM_BUT_A_HUMBLE_MITHRA_UNWORRRTHY_OF                                = 13233,  -- I am but a humble Mithra, unworrrthy of the honor of basking in your heavenly radiance, Your Holiness.
        I_FEAR_I_AM_UNFAMILIAR_WITH_THE_MAN                                   = 13234,  -- I fear I am unfamiliar with the man/woman] who stands beside you...
        THIS_IS_A_CLOSE_FRIEND_OF_MINE_AND                                    = 13235,  -- This is %, a close friend of mine and a staunch ally of the Federation war effort.
        I_SEE_THEN_THE_PLEASURE_IS_MINE                                       = 13236,  -- I see. Then the pleasure is mine, %.
        FORGIVE_US_THIS_INTRRRUSION_YOUR_HOLINESS_I_TRUST                     = 13237,  -- Forgive us this intrrrusion, Your Holiness. I trust you know whom it is we seek...
        ID_13238                                                              = 13238,  -- ...
        VERY_WELL_COME_WITH_ME                                                = 13239,  -- Very well. Come with me.
        HE_CONDUCTS_HIS_RESEARCH_DOWN_HERE_IN_THE                             = 13240,  -- He conducts his research down here...in the darkness.
        PLACE_YOUR_TRUST_IN_ME_AND_WINDURST_SHALL                             = 13241,  -- Place your trust in me, and Windurst shall escape its fate of ruin, he said. And who was I to doubt him?
        HE_PURSUES_HIS_EXPERIMENTS_LIKE_A_MAN_POSSESSED                       = 13242,  -- He pursues his experiments like a man possessed... Or so he did, until his progress stalled, for lack of a certain...vital resource.
        WHERE_WILL_IT_ALL_LEAD                                                = 13243,  -- Where will it all lead?
        IS_THE_PATH_DOWN_WHICH_HE_LEADS_US                                    = 13244,  -- Is the path down which he leads us truly one we should tread? These are questions I cannot answer.
        I_AM_FRIGHTENED_YES_FRIGHTENED_TO_THE_VERY                            = 13245,  -- I am...frightened. Yes, frightened to the very depths of my soul.
        I_HAVE_BROUGHT_YOUR_GUESTS_MAY_WE_ENTER                               = 13246,  -- I have brought your guests. May we enter?
        KARAHA_BARUHA                                                         = 13247,  -- Karaha-Baruha...?
        SO_YOU_ARE                                                            = 13248,  -- So you are...
        FORGIVE_ME_I_AM_LEHKO_HABHOKA_ADVISOR_TO                              = 13249,  -- Forgive me. I am Lehko Habhoka, advisor to the Warlock Warlord.
        DO_NOT_APOLOGIZE_IT_SEEMS_I_EVOKE_A                                   = 13250,  -- Do not apologize. It seems I evoke a similar reaction in most. Yes, I am Karaha-Baruha, Minister of the Optistery.
        THOUGH_THESE_DAYS_I_MAKE_MY_HOME_HERE                                 = 13251,  -- Though these days, I make my home here among these dusty shelves and musty tomes, as you see.
        YES_I_AM_FAMILIAR_WITH_YOUR_RRRESEARCH                                = 13252,  -- Yes. I am familiar with your...rrresearch.
        MINISTER_KARAHA_BARUHA_I_FEAR_OUR_SITUATION_HAS                       = 13253,  -- Minister Karaha-Baruha, I fear our situation has turned for the worse. The barrier has fallen in the recent attack on Fort Karugo-Narugo.
        AH_YES_I_SUSPECTED_AS_MUCH_I_FELT                                     = 13254,  -- Ah, yes...I suspected as much. I felt a disturbance in the magical forces to the east. A sudden surge, and then...silence.
        MINISTER_YOU_MUST_COMPLETE_YOUR_RESEARCH_AND_WITHOUT                  = 13255,  -- Minister, you must complete your research...and without delay.
        OH_IT_S_QUITE_COMPLETE_YOU_SEE_OR                                     = 13256,  -- Oh, it's quite complete, you see. Or it would be...were only I not deprived of that which I need most.
        YOUR_HOLINESS_PLEASE_BRING_THE_ITEM_OF_WHICH                          = 13257,  -- Your Holiness. Please bring the item of which the minister speaks.
        ID_13258                                                              = 13258,  -- ...
        NO_I_CANNOT_I_MUST_NOT_PLEASE_KARAHA                                  = 13259,  -- No! I cannot! I must not! Please, Karaha-Baruha, let us forget this madness!
        STAR_SIBYL                                                            = 13260,  -- Star Sibyl...
        ROBEL_AKBEL_MADE_ME_SWEAR_HE_SAID_THAT                                = 13261,  -- Robel-Akbel made me swear! He said that you could not be allowed to continue your work! That if you do, something...terrible...will happen to you...
        ID_13262                                                              = 13262,  -- ...
        WE_HAVE_THE_MIGHTY_WAR_WARLOCKS_AND_THE                               = 13263,  -- We have the mighty War Warlocks and the brave Mithra Mercenaries. Windurst's army is loyal and strong. Surely they can defend us from any onslaught...
        PLEASE_I_BEG_OF_YOU                                                   = 13264,  -- Please, I beg of you...
        STAR_SIBYL_SURELY_YOU_CANNOT_BE_SERIOUS                               = 13265,  -- Star Sibyl. Surely you cannot be serious.
        YOUR_WORDS_ARE_UNBECOMING_OF_YOUR_STATION_YOU                         = 13266,  -- Your words are unbecoming of your station. You are the leader of a nation. The preservation of Windurst should be your first--your only--priority.
        BUT                                                                   = 13267,  -- But...
        FORGIVE_ME                                                            = 13268,  -- Forgive me.
        WELL_SHALL_WE                                                         = 13269,  -- Well, shall we?
        ID_13270                                                              = 13270,  -- ...
        HERE_DO_WITH_IT_AS_YOU_MUST                                           = 13271,  -- Here... Do with it as you must.
        AH_YES_THE_BOOK_OF_THE_GODS_THE                                       = 13272,  -- Ah yes...the Book of the Gods. The key to my research, so long denied to me. You have my thanks.
        NOW_LET_US_PROCEED_OUR_TIME_AFTER_ALL                                 = 13273,  -- Now let us proceed. Our time, after all, is short...no?
        IT_IS                                                                 = 13274,  -- It is.
        LONG_HAVE_I_LABORED_DOWN_HERE_IN_THE                                  = 13275,  -- Long have I labored...down here in the depths where the sun dares not shine, where night and day are as one. I have but a single goal...to save Windurst from its prophesied destruction.
        I_WILL_NOT_BORE_YOU_WITH_THE_SPECIFICS                                = 13276,  -- I will not bore you with the specifics, which would be beyond your comprehension anyhow. Let it suffice to say that the deeper I delved into the ancient secrets, the clearer it became to me. They were all speaking in unison...beckoning me down a singular path.
        AND_THAT_PATH_IS                                                      = 13277,  -- And that path is...?
        THE_SAVAGE_BEAST_TAMED_BY_RIMILALA_THE_FOUNDING                       = 13278,  -- The savage beast tamed by Rimilala, the founding mother of our nation.
        YES_I_SPEAK_OF_FENRIR                                                 = 13279,  -- Yes... I speak of Fenrir.
        THE_POWER_THAT_BROUGHT_THE_FEROCIOUS_BEAST_OF                         = 13280,  -- The power that brought the ferocious beast of legend to its knees...is the only power that can save Windurst once more.
        ID_13281                                                              = 13281,  -- ...
        BUT_HOW_WAS_RIMILALA_ABLE_TO_SUBDUE_THE                               = 13282,  -- But how was Rimilala able to subdue the beast? Is this rrrecorded in the tome?
        LET_US_SEE_AHH_YES_YES                                                = 13283,  -- Let us see... Ahh, yes...yes...
        TO_ENSNARE_THE_RAGING_BEAST_RIMILALA_SUMMONED_ALL                     = 13284,  -- To ensnare the raging beast, Rimilala summoned all of her prodigious powers and channeled them into the creation of a single artifact.
        THE_MYSTIC_FETTERS_OF_SUPREME_POWER_AT_ONCE                           = 13285,  -- The mystic fetters of supreme power...at once supple as the wind and stronger than darksteel... She bestowed unto it the name...%.
        ID_13286                                                              = 13286,  -- %...
        SHE_CAST_THE_FETTERS_INTO_FULL_MOON_FOUNTAIN                          = 13287,  -- She cast the fetters into Full Moon Fountain, its arcane force propelling them high into the heavens! For an instant that lasted an eternity, all was bathed in moonlight...and when it faded, the great beast was still.
        THE_BEAST_NOW_CONQUERED_RIMILALA_USED_HER_IMMENSE                     = 13288,  -- The beast now conquered, Rimilala used her immense power not to beat it into submission...but to reach out to it with tenderness, and share its pain.
        SO_IT_WAS_THAT_THE_GREAT_BEAST_FENRIR                                 = 13289,  -- ...So it was that the Great Beast Fenrir, seer of the future, became the sworn guardian of Windurst.
        TO_PROTECT_THIS_LAND_WITH_THE_BLESSING_OF                             = 13290,  -- To protect this land with the blessing of the moon and stars for as long as he drew savage breath...
        TO_DECIPHER_THE_ANCIENT_SCRIPT_WITH_SUCH_EASE                         = 13291,  -- To decipher the ancient script with such ease... Extrrraordinary. You're every bit the genius they say.
        TO_WIELD_ONCE_MORE_THOSE_MYSTIC_FETTERS_AND                           = 13292,  -- To wield once more those mystic fetters and summon the Great Beast to our aid... Such is my one true calling.
        YET_THERE_REMAINS_A_RUB_THIS_IS_HOW                                   = 13293,  -- Yet there remains a rub. This is how the text continues...
        ITS_FATED_ROLE_COMPLETE_WAS_RENT_IN_THREE                             = 13294,  -- %, its fated role complete, was rent in three, ne'er again to meet.
        TO_FRIENDS_FOR_SAFEKEEPING_WAS_EACH_TATTER_BESTOWED                   = 13295,  -- To friends, for safekeeping, was each tatter bestowed...
        TO_THE_SMALL_TO_THE_WINGED_AND_TO                                     = 13296,  -- To the small, to the winged, and to our eight-chambered abode.
        A_RIDDLE_EVER_THE_WHIMSICAL_ONES_THESE_GODS                           = 13297,  -- A riddle? Ever the whimsical ones, these gods...
        THE_THREE_TATTERS_OF_IF_ONLY_THEY_COULD                               = 13298,  -- The three tatters of %... If only they could be recovered somehow, I am certain that I could reunite them and wield their power as Rimilala once did.
        BUT_I_CAN_ILL_AFFORD_TO_LEAVE_MY                                      = 13299,  -- But I can ill afford to leave my laboratory when there is still so much work to be done... And yet our time draws near...
        KARAHA_BARUHA_2                                                       = 13300,  -- Karaha-Baruha...
        THERE_IS_NO_NEED_TO_VEX_YOUR_PRODIGIOUS                               = 13301,  -- There is no need to vex your prodigious brrrain over such a menial task! Carry on with your research, and leave the grunt work to your loyal assistants!
        YOU_ARE_SAYING_THAT_YOU_CAN_BRING_ME                                  = 13302,  -- You are saying...that you can bring me what I seek?
        WITH_THE_INCREDIBLE_WORLD_HOPPING_ON_YOUR_SIDE                        = 13303,  -- With the incredible world-hopping % on your side, you may consider the deed as good as done! Isn't that right, %?
        IT_WOULD_SEEM_YOU_SPEAK_IN_RIDDLES_AS                                 = 13304,  -- It would seem you speak in riddles as well, Master Lehko. I know not what you imply, and yet... Yes, I am certain of it. You and your friend will not let me down.
        EVER_THE_GENIUS_I_SEE_WELL_LET_S                                      = 13305,  -- Ever the genius, I see! Well, %, let's be on our way. Time is short, and we mustn't keep the minister waiting!
        WELL_THE_BEST_INFORMATION_COMES_STRRRAIGHT_FROM_THE                   = 13306,  -- Well, the best information comes strrraight from the chocobo's mouth, I say. When you're looking for a relic to tame a beast, you ask...
        YES_WHAT_IS_IT_THIS_TIME_I_HAVE                                       = 13307,  -- Yes? What is it this time? I have pressing matters to attend to, so make it brief.
        OH_COME_NOW_YOU_OF_ALL_SHOULD_KNOW                                    = 13308,  -- Oh, come now. You of all should know that this is a matter of the utmost imporrrt.
        HMPH_VERY_WELL                                                        = 13309,  -- ...Hmph. Very well.
        KARAHA_BARUHA_SAID_THAT_ACCORDING_TO_THE_BOOK                         = 13310,  -- Karaha-Baruha said that according to the Book of the Gods, % was torn into three pieces, which were entrusted in turn to the small, the winged, and the eight-chambered abode...
        WELL_OUR_CARBUNCLE_FRIEND_HERE_HAS_KINDLY_AGRRREED                    = 13311,  -- Well, %, our Carbuncle friend here has kindly agrrreed to share his knowledge, so ask away! It won't do to go gallivanting across time and space without a few good clues at your disposal, after all.
        ID_13312                                                              = 13312,  -- ...
        WHAT_WILL_YOU_ASK_ABOUT_THE_SMALL_THE                                 = 13313,  -- What will you ask about? The small. The winged. The eight-chambered abode. Nothing at the moment.
        THE_SMALL_HMMM                                                        = 13314,  -- The small...hmmm.
        THERE_ARE_MANY_DIMINUTIVE_BEINGS_IN_THIS_WORLD                        = 13315,  -- There are many diminutive beings in this world.
        BUT_NONE_SO_ANCIENT_NOR_BONDED_SO_CLOSELY                             = 13316,  -- But none so ancient, nor bonded so closely with Altana's children, as those who call Grauberg home.
        IT_IS_SAID_THEY_EVEN_HAVE_A_PROPHECY                                  = 13317,  -- It is said they even have a prophecy. That they have been waiting since the dawn of time for their promised one.
        UNDER_A_DARK_STAR_IN_THE_BLACKEST_OF                                  = 13318,  -- Under a dark star, in the blackest of nights, he/she] will come... the light in his/her] hand illuminating the darkness.
        A_BRINGER_OF_LIGHT_HOW_CURIOUS_AS_I                                   = 13319,  -- A bringer of light? How curious. As I recall, they themselves shine rather brightly as well...
        THE_WINGS_ARE_SURELY_THE_WINGS_OF_A                                   = 13320,  -- The wings are surely the wings of a bird. And birds can only mean...yes.
        TO_THINK_THAT_IN_THOSE_TIMES_WE_COUNTED                               = 13321,  -- To think that in those times, we counted them among our frrriends...
        THAT_IS_ANCIENT_HISTORY_TODAY_THEY_WILL_SOONER                        = 13322,  -- That is ancient history. Today, they will sooner skewer you than accede to your request. Unless...
        THERE_IS_ONE_AMONG_THEM_CALLED_KAA_TORU                               = 13323,  -- There is one among them called Kaa Toru the Just. It is said he honors his word to friend and foe alike.
        BE_WARNED_THAT_HE_DOES_NOT_SUFFER_FOOLS                               = 13324,  -- Be warned that he does not suffer fools or imposters lightly. It would be wise to bring some...proof...of your integrity.
        A_STRUCTURE_OF_MANY_ROOMS_WHEREVER_COULD_THAT                         = 13325,  -- A structure of many rooms? Wherever could that be?
        FEW_BUILDINGS_REMAIN_NOW_THAT_HAVE_STOOD_SINCE                        = 13326,  -- Few buildings remain now that have stood since the Federation was born...
        I_VE_FOUND_THAT_AT_TIMES_WHEN_YOU                                     = 13327,  -- I've found that at times when you're at a loss, sometimes it's best to check rrright under your nose...
        QUITE_TRUE                                                            = 13328,  -- Quite true.
        I_CAN_THINK_OF_ONE_SUCH_PLACE_THOUGH                                  = 13329,  -- I can think of one such place, though it is like to be sealed shut these days. But that's no prrroblem for you now, is it %?
        WELL_I_TRRRUST_THAT_S_ENOUGH_TO_SET                                   = 13330,  -- Well, I trrrust that's enough to set you on your way.
        WE_HAVE_SOME_MATTERS_OF_OUR_OWN_TO                                    = 13331,  -- We have some matters of our own to research, so we shall stay here in Windurst.
        SPEAK_TO_VELDA_GALDA_BY_THE_PATH_TO                                   = 13332,  -- Speak to Velda-Galda by the path to Windurst Walls when you return. He will lead you back to Heavens Tower.
        IT_HARDLY_NEEDS_SAYING_THAT_IT_IS_NOT                                 = 13333,  -- It hardly needs saying that it is not only Karaha-Baruha and ourselves, but all of Windurst that is counting on you this time. Do be careful, and report back as soon as your search bearrrs fruit.
        YOU_RE_STILL_WANDERING_ABOUT_IS_THERE_SOMETHING                       = 13334,  -- You're still wandering about, %? Is there something we can do for you?
        HOW_ABOUT_IT_IS_THAT_ENOUGH_TO_GET                                    = 13335,  -- How about it? Is that enough to get your search starrrted?
        I_HARDLY_NEED_REMIND_YOU_THAT_ALL_OF                                  = 13336,  -- I hardly need remind you that all of Windurst is counting on you. Do take care, and report back to us here as soon as your search bearrrs fruit.
        THE_THERE_IS_NO_MISTAKING_IT                                          = 13337,  -- The %. There is no mistaking it.
        WE_ARE_ONE_STEP_CLOSER_FOR_BETTER_OR                                  = 13338,  -- We are one step closer, for better or for worse.
        I_CAN_T_HELP_BUT_WONDER_WHAT_WOULD                                    = 13339,  -- I can't help but wonder. What would happen if--Goddess forbid--Karaha-Baruha's attempt to summon the Great Beast went awrrry?
        THE_DAMAGE_WOULD_BE_GREAT_OF_THAT_THERE                               = 13340,  -- The damage would be great. Of that there can be no doubt. And I speak not merely of the buildings that would be leveled by the raging beast.
        INDEED_THOUGH_HE_MAY_HAVE_ASSUMED_A_HERMIT                            = 13341,  -- Indeed. Though he may have assumed a hermit's life, Karaha-Baruha is a Minister of the Federation, and the greatest genius this nation has ever known.
        YES_WERE_SUCH_A_TRUSTED_FIGURE_TO_SUFFER                              = 13342,  -- Yes. Were such a trusted figure to suffer a crushing defeat, the Windurstian people would feel that their greatest--their last--hope had been snuffed out like a candle. For them, the war would be as good as lost...
